# migrated from tests/cases/define_teach.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test define_teach]
# gen337: definitional teaching — mode=define of the generic teach handler
# (try_teach_form + learnable/3). The capture frame is KB data
# (learnable("definition of"/"definizione di", concept, define) in
# kb/core/intents.p0); the consumer already existed (kb_concept_def and the
# what-is path read any pred(Key, "Description")). Teaching a concept via a
# prompt makes it answerable on the next turn — no C edit, no rebuild. This is
# the cognitive structure that lets a teacher hand parrot0 a NEW concept (e.g.
# what "kb-first" means) purely in conversation. EN + IT (bilingual ratchet).
> learn the definition of kb-first: "engine fixed, knowledge learns"
< Got it - kb-first: engine fixed, knowledge learns.
> what is kb-first?
< kb-first is engine fixed, knowledge learns.
> impara la definizione di catena-cue: "una lista di parole in codice C"
< Got it - catena-cue: una lista di parole in codice C.
> cosa è catena-cue?
< catena-cue is una lista di parole in codice C.
